  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.",
    "Brown the beef brisket in batches until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes per side.",
    "Transfer the browned beef to a plate and set aside.",
    "Add more oil if necessary, then sauté the ginger until fragrant, about 2 minutes.",
    "Add the fish sauce, oyster sauce, and coconut milk, stirring to combine.",
    "Return the beef to the pot and add the beef stock, bay leaves, and green chili peppers.",
    "Bring to a boil, then cover and transfer to the oven for 2 hours, or until the beef is tender.",
    "Add the sliced fish balls and chopped bok choy to the pot and continue to simmer for another 30 minutes.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with chopped cilantro if desired."
  ],
